File: South African President Cyril Ramaphosa. AFP/Esa Alexander JOHANNESBURG - AFriforum has applied to the State Capture Commission to subpoena President Cyril Ramaphosa to appear.   Afriforum has filed an application to the State Capture Commission to subpoena President Cyril Ramaphosa to appear. #DStv03 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/souEUsnSJr It wants Ramaphosa to be cross-examined on the ANC's cadre deployment policy and also requested an opportunity to make submissions to cross-examine Ramaphosa. READ: AfriForum, Solidarity to take legal action against government This application comes on the back of the ruling party's cadre deployment committee from 2013 to 2016. AfriForum also wants to question Brian Molefe, Dudu Myeni, Pravin Gordhan, Thuli Madonsela and several others. It says the ANC's deployment policy is one of the most important factors at the State Capture Commission.